         <abstract>
            <p>A numerical procedure to compute the best uniform approximation to a given continuous function by algebraic polynomials with nonnegative rth derivative is presented and analyzed. The method is based on discretization and linear programming. Several numerical experiments are discussed.</p>
          </abstract>
